<BaseLayout
  title="Help — How to Use Agent Project Control Tower"
  description="Operational guide for the Agent Project Control Tower: how to report a phase, the double-door model, the public-data update checklist, and where to find the full docs."
>
<div class="help-doc">
  <section>
    <h2>Help — How to use this dashboard</h2>
    <p class="muted">
      Operational guide for <strong>Agent Project Control Tower</strong>. This page is rendered as part of the
      <a href="https://control-tower.conanxin.com/">live dashboard</a> — same build as
      <a href="/">Home</a> and <a href="/timeline/">Timeline</a>. It exists so you can read the workflow
      without leaving the dashboard. The full, version-controlled documentation lives in
      <a href="https://github.com/conanxin/agent-project-control-tower/tree/main/docs">the GitHub repo</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>1 · Start here</h2>
    <p>
      The control tower is a <strong>Git-backed status dashboard for multi-agent projects</strong>.
      It does not store your source code. Each tracked project lives in its own code repository.
      The control tower only tracks the project's <em>current state</em> across machines and agents.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Source code</strong> stays in the project's own repo (e.g. <code>conanxin/booktrans-desk</code>).</li>
      <li><strong>Project state</strong> lives here, as a stream of <code>PHASE_REPORT</code> / <code>REVIEW_REPORT</code> / <code>FAILURE</code> events.</li>
      <li><code>data/</code> is the <strong>private, local</strong> event store — never published.</li>
      <li><code>public-data/</code> is the <strong>human-reviewed</strong> public snapshot — this is what the dashboard renders.</li>
      <li>The dashboard itself is a static Astro site rebuilt from <code>public-data/</code> and deployed to Cloudflare Pages.</li>
      <li>Cloudflare deployment is triggered automatically on <code>git push</code>. There is no manual deploy step and no Cloudflare API token used.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2 · Core mental model</h2>
    <p>The data flow from "agent finishes work" to "dashboard updates" is:</p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Project repo</strong> — agent finishes work, pushes source code to the project's own repo.</li>
      <li><strong>tower.py report-phase</strong> — agent records a phase event to local <code>data/</code>.</li>
      <li><strong>Human / local-hermes review</strong> — opens the generated event, sanity-checks it.</li>
      <li><strong>make public-update-preflight</strong> — regenerates <code>public-data/</code> candidate + writes review artifacts under <code>artifacts/public-data-update-preflight/</code>.</li>
      <li><strong>Reviewer walks the checklist</strong> — UPDATE_SUMMARY, PUBLIC_DATA_DIFF, REDACTION_RESULT, REVIEW_CHECKLIST.</li>
      <li><strong>python3 scripts/export_public_data.py --plan config/public-data-export-plan.yml --replace</strong> — promote the candidate to <code>public-data/</code>.</li>
      <li><strong>Explicit <code>git add public-data/...</code></strong> — never <code>git add .</code>.</li>
      <li><strong>git commit + git push</strong>.</li>
      <li><strong>Cloudflare Pages auto-deploys</strong> in ~30–60 s, then CDN cache settles 60–90 s later.</li>
      <li><strong>Dashboard shows the new state</strong>.</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="muted">Every step is human-reviewed. There is no CI auto-publish, no token-based export, no auto-deploy hook beyond the static-site CDN.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3 · When to trigger an update</h2>
    <p>This is <strong>not</strong> an automatic listener. The dashboard updates when a real event happens in a tracked project. Triggers include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>BookTrans Desk reaches a new phase (e.g. <code>S14</code>, replacing the current <code>S13 / 16f38b6 / PARTIAL</code> state).</li>
      <li>Artvee Gallery reaches a new phase (e.g. <code>P3C</code>, after the current <code>P3B Daily Inspiration Digest</code>).</li>
      <li>Control tower itself reaches a new phase (e.g. <code>ACT-13</code> — which is what you are looking at right now).</li>
      <li>Any other tracked real-world project produces a state worth showing publicly.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="muted">
      Triggering the update is always a manual / semi-manual step. An agent finishes work in the project repo,
      the human or <code>local-hermes</code> runs the workflow above. Cloudflare deployment is the only fully
      automatic part.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>4 · Common workflow: report a phase</h2>
    <p>The 8-step recurring flow. This is the same flow that ACT-12 trialed end-to-end.</p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <strong>Agent finishes work in the project repo</strong> and pushes the source-code commit.
        Example: <code>git push</code> in <code>~/work/booktrans-desk</code>.
      </li>
      <li>
        In the control tower, write a <code>PHASE_REPORT</code> to local <code>data/</code>:
        <pre><code>python3 scripts/tower.py report-phase \
  --project-id booktrans-desk \
  --agent-id local-hermes \
  --phase-id S14 \
  --phase-name "New Phase Name" \
  --status PASS \
  --health green \
  --summary "One-line summary of what was done." \
  --source-repo "conanxin/booktrans-desk" \
  --source-commit &lt;commit-hash&gt; \
  --next "What's next."</code></pre>
        <span class="muted">Short templates also exist under <code>templates/telegram/</code> for one-shot command issuance.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        Run the preflight:
        <pre><code>make public-update-preflight</code></pre>
        This regenerates <code>public-data/</code> as a candidate and writes 7 review artifacts to
        <code>artifacts/public-data-update-preflight/</code>.
      </li>
      <li>
        Review the artifacts: <code>UPDATE_SUMMARY.md</code>, <code>PUBLIC_DATA_DIFF.md</code>,
        <code>REDACTION_RESULT.md</code>, <code>REVIEW_CHECKLIST.md</code>, <code>NEXT_STEPS.md</code>.
      </li>
      <li>
        If everything looks correct, promote the candidate to live <code>public-data/</code>:
        <pre><code>python3 scripts/export_public_data.py \
  --plan config/public-data-export-plan.yml --replace</code></pre>
      </li>
      <li>
        Stage <strong>only</strong> the reviewed files (no <code>git add .</code>):
        <pre><code>git add public-data/MANIFEST.json \
        public-data/registry/projects.yml \
        public-data/registry/agents.yml \
        public-data/events/*.json \
        site/index.embedded.html
git status --short</code></pre>
      </li>
      <li>
        Commit and push:
        <pre><code>git commit -m "ACT-N: short description of the update"
git push</code></pre>
      </li>
      <li>
        Wait 60–90 s for Cloudflare Pages deploy + CDN cache, then verify with the
        <a href="https://github.com/conanxin/agent-project-control-tower/blob/main/templates/checklists/online-verification-checklist.md">online verification checklist</a>.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>5 · Common commands</h2>
    <p>The most-used commands. Full reference lives in <a href="https://github.com/conanxin/agent-project-control-tower/blob/main/docs/AGENT_USAGE_PLAYBOOK.md"><code>docs/AGENT_USAGE_PLAYBOOK.md</code></a>.</p>

    <h3>Report an event</h3>
    <pre><code>python3 scripts/tower.py report-phase    --project-id ... --agent-id ... --phase-id ... --status ... --summary ...
python3 scripts/tower.py report-failure  --project-id ... --agent-id ... --summary ...
python3 scripts/tower.py report-review   --project-id ... --agent-id ... --summary ...
python3 scripts/tower.py report-handoff  --project-id ... --agent-id ... --target-agent-id ... --summary ...
python3 scripts/tower.py report-release  --project-id ... --agent-id ... --tag ... --summary ...</code></pre>

    <h3>Register a new entity (one-shot per project / per agent)</h3>
    <pre><code>python3 scripts/tower.py register-project --project-id ... --name ... --repo ... --location ... --category ...
python3 scripts/tower.py register-agent   --agent-id ... --name ... --machine ... --role ...</code></pre>

    <h3>Build, validate, refresh</h3>
    <pre><code>make public-update-preflight        # generate candidate + review artifacts
python3 scripts/export_public_data.py --plan config/public-data-export-plan.yml --replace
python3 scripts/validate.py --source public-data
python3 scripts/build_index.py --source public-data
python3 scripts/build_embedded_site.py
(cd apps/dashboard && npm run build)</code></pre>

    <h3>Command generator (preferred for multi-line / copy-paste)</h3>
    <pre><code>python3 scripts/generate_tower_command.py \
  --template templates/telegram/report-phase.txt \
  --out /tmp/cmd.sh
bash /tmp/cmd.sh</code></pre>
    <p class="muted">The generator reads <code>&lt;PLACEHOLDER&gt;</code> tokens and produces a real shell script — no manual escaping, no template/CLI drift.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>6 · Double-door model</h2>
    <p>The control tower separates <strong>writing events</strong> from <strong>publishing them publicly</strong>. This is the most important invariant.</p>

    <h3>Door 1 — any agent may write <code>data/</code></h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Each agent has its own <code>agent_id</code> and writes its own events.</li>
      <li><code>data/</code> is local + gitignored. It can contain home paths, in-progress notes, anything.</li>
      <li>A <code>PHASE_REPORT</code> or <code>FAILURE</code> in <code>data/</code> is <strong>not yet public</strong>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Door 2 — only the local-hermes / human gate exports <code>public-data/</code></h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Exporting <code>public-data/</code> requires running the ACT-11 preflight + manual review.</li>
      <li>Trial agents must <strong>not</strong> directly:
        <ul>
          <li>run <code>export_public_data.py</code> (no auto-export)</li>
          <li>run <code>git add public-data/</code> on the tower repo</li>
          <li>run <code>git push</code> on the tower repo</li>
          <li>modify <code>config/public-data-export-plan.yml</code></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Those four actions belong to the human reviewer / local-hermes.</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="muted">Why: trial agents can crash, hallucinate, or operate on stale state. The public dashboard is the public record, so the door to it is narrow on purpose.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>7 · Public-data update checklist</h2>
    <p>Before <code>git push</code>, every public-data update must pass these. ACT-11 preflight enforces most of them automatically; the rest is human review.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><input type="checkbox" disabled /> No 1-project downgrade (<code>project_count_meets_plan</code>).</li>
      <li><input type="checkbox" disabled /> BookTrans Desk still points at <code>conanxin/booktrans-desk</code> — never <code>conanxin-homepage</code>.</li>
      <li><input type="checkbox" disabled /> No <code>HP-33</code> events bleeding into BookTrans Desk's current state (<code>booktrans_no_hp33</code>).</li>
      <li><input type="checkbox" disabled /> Redaction <code>FAIL = 0</code> (no leaked tokens / IPs / home paths / <code>.env</code>).</li>
      <li><input type="checkbox" disabled /> <code>MANIFEST.json</code> matches <code>config/public-data-export-plan.yml</code> (same project_filter, agent_filter, max_events_per_project).</li>
      <li><input type="checkbox" disabled /> <code>data/</code> not staged.</li>
      <li><input type="checkbox" disabled /> <code>generated/</code> not staged (regenerated by build, not source of truth).</li>
      <li><input type="checkbox" disabled /> <code>artifacts/</code> not staged (review-only, never committed).</li>
      <li><input type="checkbox" disabled /> <code>apps/dashboard/dist/</code> not staged (regenerated by <code>npm run build</code>).</li>
      <li><input type="checkbox" disabled /> <code>git status --short</code> shows only <code>public-data/</code> + <code>site/index.embedded.html</code> + optional <code>reports/</code> + <code>docs/</code>.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>8 · Multi-machine usage</h2>
    <p>The tower is designed to be cloned onto multiple machines with multiple agents.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Every machine that wants to report events clones the control tower repo.</li>
      <li>Each agent on each machine registers a unique <code>agent_id</code> (via <code>register-agent</code>) and gets its own <code>data/events/&lt;agent_id&gt;/...</code> history.</li>
      <li>The same project can be touched by many agents over time — the timeline shows the latest phase, the latest agent, and full event history.</li>
      <li>Off-machine agents only ever write to their own <code>data/</code>. They never run <code>export_public_data.py</code>, never push the tower repo, never modify the export plan.</li>
      <li>Only <code>local-hermes</code> (notebook) or a human reviewer exports and pushes <code>public-data/</code>.</li>
      <li>Cross-machine onboarding playbook: <a href="https://github.com/conanxin/agent-project-control-tower/blob/main/docs/MULTI_MACHINE_SETUP.md"><code>docs/MULTI_MACHINE_SETUP.md</code></a>.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

